4,763 followers
9mo ‚Ä¢ Edited9 monthsIn support of the medical staff fighting to protect our health, our Cascade Designs family of brands is shifting our Seattle manufacturing to produce ASTM Level 1 masks. Once at full production, we‚Äôll be delivering up to 20,000 masks a day for 51 hospitals in the Providence Health & Services network. We‚Äôre grateful to have a team of highly skilled and incredible sewers who have shifted their priorities to respond to the critical need.

We began production on March 31, at which time we were making more than 1,000 masks per day. We hope to reach full capacity in the coming weeks, producing up to 20,000 masks each day. Our Seattle manufacturing allows us to respond quickly to the growing demand for Personal Protective Equipment (PPE). We‚Äôre equipped to manufacture ASTM Level 1 medical masks, which provide basic bacterial filtration and sub-micron particulate protection for general medical use.

The materials for the masks are being provided by , which aims to help produce 100 million masks in response to the COVID-19 crisis. We‚Äôre humbled to join their efforts to meet the needs of the heroic healthcare community. Photo credit:
