374,"""Live and work in your city, care for your people with reasonable hours, and deliver amazing outcomes for our clients. You don't have to compromise at Slalom."" Thank you for sharing Marcelo Somers!
Marcelo Somers
‚Ä¢ 3rd+
UX Manager, Inventory Management at Shopify
10mo10 months""What holds women back at work is not some unique challenge of balancing the demands of work and family but rather a general problem of overwork that prevails in contemporary corporate culture. Women and men alike suffer as a result. But women pay higher professional costs.

If we want to solve this problem, we must reconsider what we‚Äôre willing to allow the workplace to demand of all employees.""

Some eye-opening research from HBR that when companies set out to fix gender equality, and are confronted that the issue is a general culture of overwork that affects both women and men, they'll do everything they can to justify it.

Whether it be long hours, or life on the road, I've personally watched these demands tear apart families and marriages. Social expectations push women to bear it by compromising their careers, but men bear it by not being present to their families, who also suffer as a result.

Thankfully, I've ""taken the red pill"" by working for who reinvented the consulting model 20 years ago. No more grueling hours and road warrior lifestyle. Live and work in your city, care for your people with reasonable hours, and deliver amazing outcomes for our clients. You don't have to compromise.
‚Ä¶see more
What‚Äôs Really Holding Women Back?
hbr.org ‚Ä¢ 1 min read
